description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Isn’t it a beautiful thing when career and passion come together?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashdown PICU&lt;/strong&gt; are looking for like-minded enthusiastic and dedicated Registered Mental Health Nurses to lead in the delivery of quality care to individuals who are experiencing a crisis in their mental health and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closely affiliated with NAPICU, we are working to improve the care and treatment for our service user population, and help guide current and future practice within this complex field of work. Our philosophy puts the service user at the centre of their care and supports carer&#39;s and families to maximise their resource towards better lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside a supportive and cohesive team, you will have excellent communication skills, be able to demonstrate shift coordination and show competent nursing skills within the clinical area to both the registered and unregistered staff. You will be able to demonstrate effectiveness in ensuring continuity of care and implementation of trust policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developmental support will be provided through the supervision structure and ward manager. There is prospect for providing access to training, which focuses on clinical, management and leadership skills. This is in addition to receiving a comprehensive induction package on commencing employment on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Sam Dardis, Ward Manager on samantha.dardis@nhs.net or 01722 820150&lt;/p&gt;
